abstract: Pete Buttigieg held on to a narrow lead on Tuesday as Iowa Democrats released additional results from their chaotic caucuses, as former Vice President Joe Biden trailed badly in fourth place with about 71% of precincts reporting.
snippet: Pete Buttigieg held on to a narrow lead on Tuesday as Iowa Democrats released additional results from their chaotic caucuses, as former Vice President Joe Biden trailed badly in fourth place with about 71% of precincts reporting.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Pete Buttigieg held on to a narrow lead on Tuesday as Iowa Democrats released additional results from their chaotic caucuses, as former Vice President Joe Biden trailed badly in fourth place with about 71% of precincts reporting.
headline_main: Buttigieg Holds Narrow Lead in Iowa, Biden Lags in Democrats' Updated Results
headline_print_headline: Buttigieg Holds Narrow Lead in Iowa, Biden Lags in Democrats' Updated Results

abstract: State attorneys general investigating Alphabet Inc's Google unit met on Tuesday with U.S. Justice Department officials to coordinate efforts to probe the search and advertising giant, officials told Reuters.
snippet: State attorneys general investigating Alphabet Inc's Google unit met on Tuesday with U.S. Justice Department officials to coordinate efforts to probe the search and advertising giant, officials told Reuters.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — State attorneys general investigating Alphabet Inc's Google unit met on Tuesday with U.S. Justice Department officials to coordinate efforts to probe the search and advertising giant, officials told Reuters.
headline_main: State AGs, Justice Department Discuss Google Antitrust Probe
headline_print_headline: State AGs, Justice Department Discuss Google Antitrust Probe

abstract: CONCORD, N.H. — Day 2 of the weeklong sprint to the New Hampshire primary began early Wednesday as several of the Democratic presidential candidates, including Pete Buttigieg and Senator Amy Klobuchar, discussed climate change and clean energy at a daylong forum here.
lead_paragraph: CONCORD, N.H. — Day 2 of the weeklong sprint to the New Hampshire primary began early Wednesday as several of the Democratic presidential candidates, including Pete Buttigieg and Senator Amy Klobuchar, discussed climate change and clean energy at a daylong forum here.

headline_main: Buttigieg, Klobuchar and several others speak at a climate forum.

abstract: Pete Buttigieg held a slight lead over Bernie Sanders in the opening contest of the Democratic race for the presidential nomination, according to partial results released by the Iowa Democratic Party.
snippet: Pete Buttigieg held a slight lead over Bernie Sanders in the opening contest of the Democratic race for the presidential nomination, according to partial results released by the Iowa Democratic Party.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — Pete Buttigieg held a slight lead over Bernie Sanders in the opening contest of the Democratic race for the presidential nomination, according to partial results released by the Iowa Democratic Party.
headline_main: Partial Iowa Results Give Buttigieg Slight Edge Over Sanders
headline_print_headline: Partial Iowa Results Give Buttigieg Slight Edge Over Sanders

abstract: Senators Bernie Sanders, Elizabeth Warren and Amy Klobuchar will leave New Hampshire and zip back to Washington today for the final moments of President Trump’s impeachment trial.
lead_paragraph: Senators Bernie Sanders, Elizabeth Warren and Amy Klobuchar will leave New Hampshire and zip back to Washington today for the final moments of President Trump’s impeachment trial.
headline_main: Senators skipped Trump’s speech, but they’ll vote to convict him.

abstract: A day and a half later, we’re still waiting for final results from the Iowa caucuses. But with 71 percent of precincts reporting as of late Tuesday night, Pete Buttigieg held a narrow lead — having earned the most “state delegate equivalents.”
lead_paragraph: A day and a half later, we’re still waiting for final results from the Iowa caucuses. But with 71 percent of precincts reporting as of late Tuesday night, Pete Buttigieg held a narrow lead — having earned the most “state delegate equivalents.”
headline_main: Here’s where we stand on Iowa results.

abstract: MANCHESTER, N.H. — The leading Democratic candidates are beginning the day in New Hampshire, which holds its primary next Tuesday, even as they keep an eye on results from Monday’s caucuses in Iowa.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — The leading Democratic candidates are beginning the day in New Hampshire, which holds its primary next Tuesday, even as they keep an eye on results from Monday’s caucuses in Iowa.
headline_main: The candidates fan out across New Hampshire.

abstract: Results trickled in, and the candidates recalibrated. This is your morning tip sheet.
snippet: Results trickled in, and the candidates recalibrated. This is your morning tip sheet.
lead_paragraph: Pat Provencher waited for a Pete Buttigieg campaign event to begin at Laconia Middle School in New Hampshire on Tuesday.
